seo_description:
Khushi, a humble and hardworking waitress, is shattered when her longtime boyfriend Raj publicly humiliates and betrays her for the wealthy and arrogant Sanjana Mehra — heiress to a powerful restaurant empire. In a moment of heartbreak and humiliation, Khushi is rescued by three mysterious men, who turn out to be her long-lost brothers from the influential Oberoi family. Separated from her family as a child, Khushi is reunited with them after 19 years on the emotional day of Rakshabandhan.

With the support of her brothers — a CEO, a popstar, and a boxer — Khushi begins to rebuild her life. She sets out to take revenge not with violence, but by building her own restaurant empire, aiming to outshine Sanjana on her own terms. Along the way, Khushi unexpectedly reconnects with Sid Wadia, a charming billionaire she once saved, who may just be the man to heal her wounds.

As Khushi rises from betrayal to power, she faces drama, rivalry, love, and redemption in a journey that transforms her from a discarded lover to a fearless queen.
